#176
North Moat Path~
A narrow track hugs the north wall of the moat here, the dark water lapping
quietly just a few feet below. Moss clings to the stone edging, making the
footing treacherous. Arrow slits can be seen high up in the keep's outer wall
to the south, suggesting the path is watched. The smell of stagnant water
hangs thick in the air.
