#186
South Moat Path~
The southern face of the keep looms overhead as the moat path curves along
here. This side of the keep is less maintained; crabgrass and nettles crowd
the edges of the path. The moat water below seems shallower on this side,
revealing glimpses of rusted iron grates set into the stone below. Chains
dangle from them, their purpose unclear.
