#187
South Moat Path~
A section of the south moat path runs along a low wall, barely knee-height,
offering a dizzying view of the dark water below. Old carvings in the stone
wall to the south depict scenes of magical combat, worn smooth by wind and
rain. The sound of the water is loud here, echoing oddly off the walls.
