#213
East Guard Tower - Ground Floor~
The base of the eastern guard tower is a cramped, functional space. Hooks
along the walls hold spare cloaks and equipment bags. A narrow spiral stair
winds upward through the ceiling to the tower top. A small hearth in one
corner holds a banked fire, and a battered table bears the remains of a
meal. The smell of woodsmoke and leather is thick. The captain's duty board
on the wall shows patrols and shift times.
