#214
East Guard Tower - Top~
The top of the east tower offers a commanding view of the courtyard below
and the surrounding countryside. Crenellations line the parapet, their stone
worn by years of wind and weather. A signal horn hangs on a peg, ready for
use. The captain of the guards is stationed here, sharp eyes scanning the
grounds with practiced suspicion. A stack of crossbow bolts beside a loaded
weapon suggests readiness for trouble.
