West Guard Tower - Ground Floor~
The base of the western guard tower is utilitarian in the extreme. Weapon
racks hold spare spears, bows and quivers in neat order. A locked iron chest
sits beneath the stair, chained to a ring in the floor. The spiral staircase
above groans faintly as a guard paces on the tower top. A narrow window slit
lets in a thin blade of daylight. The air smells of oil and iron.
