#216
West Guard Tower - Top~
The top of the west tower commands a view of the road approach and the
outer moat. Crossbow bolts are stacked in a wooden case, and a fire basket
for signals stands cold and unlit. The tower's keeper, an unusually large
and scarred guard, stands here — his size and the way his eyes track every
movement below mark him as something beyond an ordinary soldier. Old battle
trophies adorn the parapet wall: a cracked helm, a broken sword, a scorched
piece of banner.
