#218
Entry Vestibule~
A vaulted antechamber separates the outer entrance from the keep's interior.
The floor is polished black marble, reflecting the globe-lights floating
near the ceiling. A large portrait of the Keep's founder hangs on the east
wall, his eyes seeming to follow visitors with unsettling attention. Staircases
descend to the left and right into gloom — one leading down to the basement,
the other to service areas. The air is cool and carries the faint smell of
parchment and arcane reagents.
