#219
Entrance to the Rotunda~
A broad archway of carved white stone opens onto the keep's famous rotunda.
The arch is decorated with inlaid silver runes that pulse faintly with a soft
inner light. The floor transitions from black marble to a mosaic depicting
the keep's history — battles, discoveries, and the faces of generations of
masters. Globes of cold magelight float near the high ceiling. The smell of
incense and reagents is strong here. Scholars and servants move purposefully
through the space.
