#223
Rotunda - Inner East~
A narrower extension of the eastern rotunda passage leads to a locked door
set into the keep's inner wall. The door is heavy iron, set with a small
barred window at head height. Sounds of chanting and the occasional soft
thump come faintly through the door. The floor in front of it has been worn
by many feet. A small brass plaque beside the door reads "Inner Sanctum —
Authorised Persons Only." The air thrums faintly with restrained power.
