#224
Rotunda - South Alcove~
The southern alcove of the rotunda is furnished as a waiting area, with
cushioned benches along the curved wall. A low table holds a tray of
refreshments — a ceramic pitcher, cups, and a plate of small cakes — maintained
by magical means and always fresh. Portraits of past masters of the keep line
the walls above the benches, their painted eyes serene. The room smells of
fresh pastry and warm stone.
