#225
Basement - Landing~
A steep stone stair descends from the vestibule above into the basement of
the keep. The air here is noticeably colder and carries the heavy smell of
damp stone, mildew, and something sharper — perhaps old reagents stored below.
The walls glisten with moisture. A single torch bracket on the wall holds a
guttering torch. Old crates and barrels have been shoved against the wall at
the foot of the stairs, as if someone needed to move quickly.
