#227
Basement - East Corridor~
The eastern corridor of the basement is darker than the main passage; only
every second torch bracket holds a lit torch. The walls here have been carved
with crude warding symbols, overlapping in places as if different hands made
them at different times. The sound of distant moaning comes faintly from
further east — perhaps just the wind through some gap in the foundation,
perhaps not. The air smells of rust and old fear.
