#228
Entrance to Prison~
A heavy iron door set in the basement wall marks the entrance to the keep's
prison. The door is scarred with deep scratches at about waist height — from
the inside, it would appear, based on the direction of the gouges. A key hook
beside the door is empty; whoever holds the key last took it with them. A
small observation slit in the door allows a view into the corridor beyond.
The smell of unwashed humanity and old misery seeps through the gaps.
