#229
Prison Cell Block~
A short corridor holds three iron-barred cells, two on each side. Most are
empty, their straw pallets rotting, but one contains the slumped figure of
a forgotten prisoner who has long since ceased to be a prisoner in any
meaningful sense. Chains hang from the walls and shackle rings are set into
the floor. Something skitters in the darkness at the far end of the corridor.
The cell block boss — a haggard, dangerous man who has survived by cunning —
lurks here, hostile to outsiders, protective of his domain.
~
