#230
Wine Cellar~
The keep's wine cellar is a cool, vaulted space stacked floor to ceiling
with racks of dusty bottles. Labels in several languages indicate vintages
from distant lands. A tasting table in the center holds an uncorked bottle
and two cups — someone was here recently. A few bottles have been broken on
the floor, their dark stains soaking into the stone. The smell of old wine
is overwhelming and not entirely unpleasant. A battered ledger on the table
tracks the cellar's inventory, with several recent entries crossed out.
~
