#231
Entrance to the Foyer~
A wide archway with a heavy curtain of deep blue velvet separates this
entrance passage from the grand foyer beyond. The curtain bears the keep's
sigil in silver thread, faded but still recognisable. Two ornamental suits
of armour stand as sentinels to either side of the archway, though their
blank visors reveal nothing within. The floor here is polished stone, and
the sound of voices and footsteps from the foyer beyond drifts through the
curtain. The air smells of candle wax and old wood.
