#234
Foyer - North Central~
The northern section of the foyer narrows toward the upper keep's entrance.
The walls here are hung with trophy weapons and shields, each bearing a
small plaque naming their former owner and the circumstances of their
capture. The floors are slightly worn along a path from south to north,
worn down by generations of feet. A wizard's servant can be seen polishing
the display cases that hold smaller trophies and curios.
