Foyer Lobby - Southwest~
A south-west alcove off the foyer serves as an informal waiting area for
those seeking audience with the keep's master. Uncomfortable wooden chairs
line the wall, most occupied by petitioners with the patient, hollow look
of those who have been waiting a long time. A notice on the wall declares
that the master sees visitors by appointment only. The smell of candle smoke
and anxious people is thick here.
