#237
Foyer Lobby - Northeast~
A small northeast lobby off the foyer holds a pair of reading desks and a
low bookcase. The books are reference works — histories, maps, legal texts —
intended for use by visitors awaiting audience. Several have been left open
and face-down, their spines quietly suffering. A small window here overlooks
an inner courtyard, letting in natural light and the sound of birds. The air
smells of old leather bindings.
