#238
Foyer Lobby - Southeast~
The southeast corner of the foyer lobby is given over to a small records
alcove. Iron-bound chests of documents line the walls, each sealed with a
wax stamp. A writing desk holds an open ledger and a quill. The keep's
archivist, a meticulous and often irritable individual, has their domain
here and does not welcome casual visitors who disturb their work. The smell
of old parchment and ink is almost physical.
