supplies between the keep's various sections. Heavy curtains along one wall
hide utility doors and storage alcoves. The floor is slightly scuffed from
constant foot traffic, and a faint smell of cooked food and cleaning
solution drifts through. A servant's bell-pull hangs near the south wall,
its brass fitting polished bright by use.
