The eastern wing of the foyer opens into a spacious hall used for small
gatherings and briefings. Rows of chairs face a raised speaking platform
at the north end. A chalkboard on the platform is covered in diagrams and
equations, still fresh. Scrolls of parchment have been left on many of
the chairs as if a lecture ended abruptly. The smell of chalk dust and
candle wax lingers. Magelight globes float near the ceiling.
