are drawn across the windows, blocking the daylight. The furniture here is
older, showing signs of disuse. Dust has gathered in the corners, and the
candles in the brackets are burned low. A locked door in the western wall
bears a strange circular marking, unlike the keep's usual heraldry. The air
has a faint charge to it, like before a lightning storm.
