#244
North - Passage to the Inner Keep~
Beyond the locked northern door, a short passage leads toward the inner
keep proper. The air here is noticeably different — stiller, heavier, charged
with old magic. The walls are plain undressed stone, lacking the decoration
of the foyer. Faint runes glow at the base of the walls at regular intervals,
their purpose unclear. The door behind you clicks shut with a sound of
finality. There is no obvious way to open it from this side.
