#259
Inner Keep - Dead End~
The northern passage through the inner keep ends abruptly at a blank stone
wall. However, the wall is not as blank as it first appears: faint seams
outline a doorway that has been sealed, and crude scratched text above it
reads "NOT YET" in the keep's formal script. It seems this passage was meant
to lead further, but whatever lies beyond this sealed door has not yet been
made accessible. For now, this is the end of the road. The air hums with
anticipation, as if the keep itself knows something is waiting to be
completed.
